&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src="https://k4i.top/images/posts/cycle-finding/tortoise-and-hare.svg"
alt="Figure 1: tortoise and hare"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="figure-number"&gt;Figure 1: &lt;/span&gt;tortoise and hare&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hare and tortoise both starts from point &lt;strong&gt;Start&lt;/strong&gt;, at speed of \(2\) and \(1\) respectively. They&amp;rsquo;ll meet at some point in the cycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when they meet, hare traveled \(S_2 - S_{1}\) more points than tortoise. We have: (\(\lambda\) is the cycle length)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[&lt;br /&gt;
S_{2} - S_{1} = 0 = S_{1} = x + m \pmod{\lambda}&lt;br /&gt;
